Gate the "give access to main menu" escape hatch in exitCurrentGuiMode() so it is
skipped while the companion owns the conversation on the bottom screen - i.e. when
EITHER OpenMW's in-game Hide UI is active (companionHudEnabled() == false) OR the
Conversation Game UI element is in DS mode (companionDsConversation() == true).

When a forced dialogue choice is pending (e.g. a guard's Pay Fine / Go to Jail /
Resist Arrest confrontation), DialogueWindow::exit() returns false because
DialogueManager::isInChoice() is true. Pressing B on the controller routes
(ControllerManager::gamepadToGuiControl, B case) to WindowManager::exitCurrentGuiMode(),
whose vanilla fallback pushes GM_MainMenu when a window refuses to exit. When the native
dialogue window is hidden and the companion (bottom) screen is the conversation surface,
this "escape hatch" surfaces as the pause menu opening instead of the player answering
the choice on the companion.

The previous version of this patch gated only on companionHudEnabled(). That was
insufficient: DS conversation mode hides the native dialogue window via
companionDsConversation() (a per-element DS flag pushed from Kotlin's
"game_ui_conversation"), independently of mHudEnabled - so with Hide UI off but
Conversation in DS mode, companionHudEnabled() returned true and the fallback still
fired. The condition now checks both: fire the fallback only when the window is really
the top-screen surface (Hide UI off AND Conversation Vanilla).

companionDsConversation() is already declared inside namespace MWGui by
companion-hide-dialogue-on-hideui.patch (applied earlier in the chain); it is
re-declared here at file scope alongside companionHudEnabled so both have matching
extern "C" declarations and non-Android fallbacks (companionHudEnabled -> true,
companionDsConversation -> false) that reproduce vanilla behaviour on desktop.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -130,6 +130,29 @@
 // cursor" option is off; used to keep the menu-cursor path from re-enabling the
 // top-screen cursor in GUI modes (including GM_Dialogue).
 extern "C" bool companionCursorEnabled();
+#endif
+
+#ifdef __ANDROID__
+// COMPANION: both defined in androidmain.cpp. companionHudEnabled() returns false
+// while OpenMW's in-game Hide UI is active; companionDsConversation() returns true
+// while the Conversation Game UI element is in DS mode (the native dialogue window is
+// suppressed so the companion bottom screen is the sole conversation surface). Used in
+// exitCurrentGuiMode() to suppress the vanilla "give access to main menu" escape hatch
+// when a forced dialogue choice refuses to exit, so pressing B on the companion dialogue
+// no longer pops the pause menu; the player must answer the choice on the companion. The
+// hatch is skipped when EITHER Hide UI is active OR DS conversation mode is active, since
+// DS mode hides the window independently of Hide UI (companionDsConversation, not mHudEnabled).
+extern "C" bool companionHudEnabled();
+extern "C" bool companionDsConversation();
+#else
+static inline bool companionHudEnabled()
+{
+    return true;
+}
+static inline bool companionDsConversation()
+{
+    return false;
+}
 #endif
 
 namespace MWGui
@@ -1314,7 +1337,16 @@
             if (!window->exit())
             {
                 // unable to exit window, but give access to main menu
-                if (!MyGUI::InputManager::getInstance().isModalAny() && getMode() != GM_MainMenu)
+                // COMPANION: skip this vanilla escape hatch when EITHER Hide UI is active
+                // OR Conversation is in DS mode. In both cases the native dialogue window
+                // is hidden and the companion bottom screen owns the conversation, so a B
+                // press on a forced choice (exit() refuses mid-choice) must NOT pop the
+                // pause menu; instead B is a no-op and the choice is answered on the
+                // companion. DS mode suppresses the window via companionDsConversation()
+                // independently of mHudEnabled, so both flags must be checked. Start still
+                // opens the pause menu (separate input path).
+                if (!MyGUI::InputManager::getInstance().isModalAny() && getMode() != GM_MainMenu
+                    && companionHudEnabled() && !companionDsConversation())
                     pushGuiMode(GM_MainMenu);
                 return;
             }
